<section os="osx" id="sec.dmg_inst">
  <title id="title.dmg_inst">Installation from Disk Images</title>

  <section>
    <title>Introduction</title>
    
    <para>
      Installation from a disk image consists of the following steps:
      <orderedlist>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Downloading a disk image, documentation, and sample
	  data sets.</para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Installing SCIRun from a disk image.</para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Installing SCIRun's sample data sets.</para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Installing SCIRun's documentation.</para>
	</listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </para>

  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Downloading</title>
    <para>
      From <acronym>SCI</acronym>'s <ulink
      url="http://software.sci.utah.edu/archive_entry.html">software
      archive</ulink> page download the following files:

      <itemizedlist>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    <filename>Blah blah blah</filename>
	  </para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    <filename>SCIRunData.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz</filename>
	    (or
	    <filename>FusionData.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz</filename>
	    if also downloading the Fusion specific RPM).
	  </para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    <filename>SCIRunDocs.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz</filename>
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </para>

  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Installing</title>
    <para>blah blah blah</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>SCIRun's Sample Data Sets</title>
    <para>
      Install the sample data sets into
      <filename>/usr/local</filename>.  Administrative privilages are
      required.
    </para>
    <para>
      Type:
      <literallayout class="monospaced">
sudo gunzip -c SCIRunData.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz | (cd /usr/local &amp;&amp; tar xf -)
      </literallayout>
     You will be asked for your login password.  The above command
     creates <filename>/usr/local/SCIRunData</filename>, the sample
     data sets directory.
    </para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>SCIRun's Documentation</title>
    <para>
      The following procedure installs the documentation in the
      directory <filename>/usr/local</filename>.  Administrative
      privilages are required.
    </para>
    <para>
      Type:
      <literallayout class="monospaced">
sudo gunzip -c SCIRunDocs.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz | (cd /usr/local &amp;&amp; tar xf -)
      </literallayout>
      You will be asked for your login password.  The above command
      will create
      <filename>/usr/local/SCIRunDocs.<!--%= doc.version %--></filename>,
      the SCIRun documentation directory.
    </para>
    <para>
      Open <filename>/usr/local/SCIRunDocs.<!--%= doc.version %-->/doc/index.html</filename>
      with a web browser to view SCIRun's online documentation.
    </para>
  </section>

</section>
